Foram Mehta:

"Founded in 2013 by Rebecca Rockefeller and Liesl Clark, the Buy Nothing Project began as an experimental hyper-local gift economy on Bainbridge Island, Washington. It has since become nothing short of a global movement, with thousands of groups in 30 countries. There are both official groups that adhere to the same principles, and more unofficial ones inspired by the original idea."

